            <div type="content">
                <div type="index">
                <p>
                    <specList>
                        <specDesc key="rs"/>
                    </specList>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <p>Important: <gi>rs</gi> should be specified by a <att>type</att> attribute, whose value(s) listed here are the only being currently handled by SigiDoc/EFES
                    autority lists and they should be used as they appear here.</p>
                <p>Intended for religious, political, military, economical, etc. terminology / Remarkable expressions.</p>
                <p>Marian terms:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <rs type="marianTerm" subtype="appellative" ref="marianTerms.xml#Δέσποινα">Δέσποινα</rs> (other ex.: Theotoke in the invocation, or vocative in the legend; different from label)
                    <rs type="marianTerm" subtype="label" ref="marianTerms.xml#..."></rs> (i.e. the name of the Virgin’s type inscribed on the seal [in the field], different from appellative)
                    <rs type="marianTerm" subtype="sigla" ref="marianTerms.xml#..."></rs> (ex.: ΜP ΘV)
                </egXML>
                <p>Christ-related terms:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <rs type="christTerm" subtype="appellative"  ref="christTerms.xml#..."></rs>
                    <rs type="christTerm" subtype="label"  ref="christTerms.xml#..."></rs>
                    <rs type="christTerm" subtype="sigla"  ref="christTerms.xml#..."></rs>
                </egXML>
                <p>Saints-related terms:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <rs type="saintsTerm" subtype="appellative" ref="saintsTerms.xml#..."></rs> (Archistrategos for Michael, martyr, ...)
                    <rs type="saintsTerm" subtype="label" ref="saintsTerms.xml#..."></rs> (i.e. the name of the saint’s type inscribed on the seal [in the field], different from saint's name; the adjective hagios should be included in the tag)
                    <rs type="saintsTerm" subtype="sigla" ref="saintsTerms.xml#..."></rs> (ex.: Μ Χ)
                    <rs type="saintsTerm" subtype="name" ref="saintsTerms.xml#..."></rs> (for ex., in an invocation in the legend; different from saint's label)
                </egXML>
                <p>Important: the attribute <att>subtype</att> is paramount in order to show in the Indices the difference among the various types of terms.</p>
                <p>With the <att>subtype</att> 'appellative' should also be tagged the adressees of the invocations, the full text of which are however contained in a separate index (see "<ref target="SigiDoc_indexing-invocation.html">Invocations</ref>").</p>
                <p>Other examples:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <rs type="ecclesiastical" ref="">ποιμήν</rs>
                    <rs type="devotional" ref="">δοῦλος τῆς Θεοτόκου</rs> (connected to the seal's owner)
                    <rs type="divinity" ref="">Κύριε</rs> (Trinity, different names for Christ, Theos, Cross)
                    <rs type="genealogical" ref=""></rs> (only for explicit genealogical references)
                </egXML>
                <p>And so on... The choice of what kind of miscellaneous terms to index is a project’s decision.</p>
                <p>The spelling should be normalised in the authority list.</p>
            </div>
